originalText.text: I had a very enjoyable, professional and productive visit. From the reception to my actual session I had a very professional,  knowledgeable and informative Dr. I would recommend hands down this place to anyone looking a for a great Psychologist. This place is clean, safe and it has wheel chair access which is a plus.

originalText.text: I highly don’t recommend. Been here for a year and change  trying it out and still the  Services here are still poor. Been changed multiple times with psychiatrist and therapist yet no growth. They don’t have same consistent workers working here and you can see that the workers here don’t like the job themselves. Front desk have attitude, will make you wait long, one of them body shame as well. They are very strict with the lateness but they never start according to schedule either. If a worker is telling you personally that they have been doing there job for years and left this place in less than about 3 months should tell you that this isn’t a the right nor fit environment for you. Your mental health is important and you should never settle for less.

originalText.text:
The best staff. They practice with there hearts. Dr.Hernandez he will take care of you. No matter who you are. He listens to your case and pin points your problem. Even though the wait time is long but you need to understand you can’t have everything meaning once you’re with him all focus is on you. He will not rush you out because he has a line waiting. You’re not just a number on a list you’re his patient and you matter.
I highly recommend him he was recommended to me. Finally I have a MD who listens and who cares.

originalText.text: The place is nice some of the staff is great. Some of the others not so much. The wait time is a bit much. I had to wait two hours after my appointment time before i got to see anyone. Just make sure if you have an appointment you are free all day.
